The defendant Nichole Michelle Muex was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nichole Michelle Muex in court with attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. 

Defendant made all appointments, all tests are negative, and completed letter of apology. Defendant completed community service and paid restitution.   The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.
On motion of the state, the court amended the charge to Theft-Movable Property, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a), a class A Misdemeanor.   Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.

AS TO COUNT 1 AMENDED
Court sentenced defendant to serve  3 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 3 days served; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 6/26/2015 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept. Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.
